section.title: Chief Complaint And Reason For Visit

paragraph.content: visual field defect follow up (chief complaint). Description: The 62 year old male presents for evaluation of visual field defect follow up in the right eye and left eye. It started about 1 week(s) ago. The onset was gradual. VA not affected. The symptom is constant. Patient denies eye pain. Patient states vision unchanged. States he went to ER as directed. Have follow up with PCP scheduled. Unable to perform HVF 30-2 today due to patient neck brace and neck pain.

The 62 year old male presents for evaluation of routine exam in the right eye and left eye. The onset was gradual. It affects distance vision. The symptom is constant. The condition is described as blurring. Patient denies eye pain. Patient state he have trouble seeing far away. Near is ok. C/O burning, flashes and spots that comes and goes. Not using any gtts.
